                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.011/5–946</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposed Revision to <gloss target="#t_SWNCC1">SWNCC</gloss>
                        228/2</hi>
                    <note n="92" xml:id="d193fn1">Transmitted by General Hilldring to the
                        State-War-Navy Coordinating Committee on May 9 for consideration. This
                        paragraph was not adopted at the 40th meeting of <gloss target="#t_SWNCC1"
                            >SWNCC</gloss> on May 9 and was dropped at the 41st meeting on June 27
                        after General McCoy had expressed disapproval.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1946-05-09">May 9, 1946</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>2. If the Japanese people should desire to adopt a new Constitution through the
                    medium of a constituent assembly, a specially elected Diet, or a popular
                    referendum, they should not be discouraged from so doing.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
